                    Unlike most major moons orbiting Saturn, Phoebe is very dark
                    and reflects only 6 percent of the sunlight it receives. Its
                    darkness and irregular, retrograde orbit suggest Phoebe is
                    most likely a captured object. A captured object is a
                    celestial body that is trapped by the gravitational pull of
                    a much bigger body, generally a planet. Phoebe's darkness,
                    in particular, suggests that the small moon comes from the
                    outer solar system, an area where there is plenty of dark
                    material.
